        <h1 class="max-w-3xl font-display font-bold text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-slate-100 leading-tight tracking-tight mb-6">
          Why Prompt Injection Hits Harder in MCP: Scope Constraints and Blast Radius
        </h1>
        <p class="max-w-3xl text-lg text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          Prompt injection is more dangerous in MCP when tools are action-capable by design and the server leaves input scope, tenant boundaries, and post-call evidence too loose to contain the damage.
        </p>
